    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNvim has healthchecks but no \"active\" performance monitoring. There are some basic active monitoring approaches that would be low-cost yet extremely high-value.\n\nFor example, a plugin may spawn numerous processes and Nvim \"slows down\" mysteriously. Or [LSP is misconfigured](https://old.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/1oja5h8/neovim_is_eating_100_gb_of_memory/), so it spawns a new language server for every buffer instead of reusing the server.\n\nRelated:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34704\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEnhance the `vim.health` interface to allow programmatic checks instead of just human-readable checks.\n\nImplement a basic health check that fails if the same LSP server is spawned too many times.\n\nImplement other basic checks for obviously-bad behavior.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
