        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Coming back to this, the idea is to have an \"evaluator\" and a bunch of \"checkers\". The evaluator would run these checkers on a 30s time interval (vim.uv). Each checker is responsible for querying a given metric and comparing against a threshold and returning the result to the evaluator. In case we detect and anomaly i.e exceed the threshold, we can then emit the notification and display it via cmdline, msg or statusline. Apart from the behavior we track by default, plugin authors should be able to write their own checkers for any behavior they believe would benefit from active monitoring.\n\nThe main blocker for me is classifying something as \"bad behavior\". Apart from some easy ones like lsp instances, jobs and active buffer instances I cant think of other behavior that warrants active monitoring. Would appreciate some community input in that.\nDo let me know if this sounds too naive or if there is a better way to go about this. \n\ncc: @justinmk ",
